Jeff Wicks, News24(File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - A Durban man is fighting for his life after he was shot in the chest during what appears to have been a botched hijacking in KwaDabeka on Wednesday, paramedics said."On arrival, we found the man in a critical state having sustained a single gunshot wound. Medics immediately initiated care and set about trying to stabilise the man," Rescue Care spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said.Jamieson said the 25-year-old was then rushed by ambulance to a Durban hospital where he remained in a critical condition. He said the circumstances leading up to the shooting remained unclear. Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said police were investigating a case of hijacking.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.